ivardefs.name: category_
ivardefs.desc: A code that classifies the clinical discipline, department or diagnostic service that created the report (e.g. cardiology, biochemistry, hematology, MRI). This is used for searching, sorting and display purposes.

ivardefs.name: code
ivardefs.desc: A code or name that describes this diagnostic report.

ivardefs.name: conclusion
ivardefs.desc: Concise and clinically contextualized summary conclusion (interpretation/impression) of the diagnostic report.

ivardefs.name: conclusionCode_
ivardefs.desc: One or more codes that represent the summary conclusion (interpretation/impression) of the diagnostic report.

ivardefs.name: encounter
ivardefs.desc: The healthcare event  (e.g. a patient and healthcare provider interaction) which this DiagnosticReport is about.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: Identifiers assigned to this report by the performer or other systems.

ivardefs.name: imagingStudy_
ivardefs.desc: One or more links to full details of any imaging performed during the diagnostic investigation. Typically, this is imaging performed by DICOM enabled modalities, but this is not required. A fully enabled PACS viewer can use this information to provide vie

ivardefs.name: issued
ivardefs.desc: The date and time that this version of the report was made available to providers, typically after the report was reviewed and verified.

ivardefs.name: media_
ivardefs.desc: A list of key images associated with this report. The images are generally created during the diagnostic process, and may be directly of the patient, or of treated specimens (i.e. slides of interest).

ivardefs.name: performer_
ivardefs.desc: The diagnostic service that is responsible for issuing the report.

ivardefs.name: presentedForm_
ivardefs.desc: Rich text representation of the entire result as issued by the diagnostic service. Multiple formats are allowed but they SHALL be semantically equivalent.

ivardefs.name: resultsInterpreter_
ivardefs.desc: The practitioner or organization that is responsible for the report's conclusions and interpretations.

ivardefs.name: result_
ivardefs.desc: [Observations](observation.html)  that are part of this diagnostic report.

ivardefs.name: specimen_
ivardefs.desc: Details about the specimens on which this diagnostic report is based.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of the diagnostic report.

ivardefs.name: subject
ivardefs.desc: The subject of the report. Usually, but not always, this is a patient. However, diagnostic services also perform analyses on specimens collected from a variety of other sources.
